comments.content:
An analysis of the mevalonate branch of the cholesterol biosynthesis pathway, and a set of inhibitors directed against targets in this pathway. Inhibitors which have been found for Homo Sapiens are coloured red, those found for Rattus norvegicus orange.

View more details on where these reactions in the cell take place at [https://www.wikipathways.org/index.php/Pathway:WP4190]. View the broader scope of cholesterol metabolism at [https://www.wikipathways.org/index.php/Pathway:WP430].
